race.description: Sandi Bradford Memorial Qtis Three-Years-Old Handicap
race.comment: FABULANTES (1) came off a five-week let-up last start and produced a real eye-catcher, coming from last at one stage to be beaten half a length over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast. Looking for this trip now and with that last run under the belt he looks the testing material. CERTIFIED COPY (2) has been freshened up since a moderate effort over 1200m at Ipswich on 3 January. In a better race today but drops 6.5kgs after Williams' claim. Draws an ideal gate so there is every chance he can bounce back to form. READY FOR AIMEE (9) clocked in third in that same race on the Sunshine Coast last start. Been in work for a while but continues to race well. BETTERLUCKNEXTTIME (3) was strong late over 1200m last time and can improve out to this trip.
